1. @Component - creates bean

2. @SpringBootApplication
	- combines 3 Spring annotations
	- used on the main class of Spring boot application
	- @ComponentScan :
		- scanning components(component,repository,beans,controller,services)

	- @EnableAutoConfiguration :
		- enable auto configuration
		- automatically configures the spring boot application based on dependencies in classpath


	- @SpringBootConfiguration :
		- configure spring boot defaults
		- similar to @Configuration
3. @Autowired
	- enables automatic dependency injection
	- allow spring to inject required beans(dependencies)

4. @Controller
	- marks a class as controller, which is handling the HTTP requests

5. @ResponseBody
	- indicated that return value of method directly into the response body
6. @RestController
	- combines @Controller and @ResponseBody
	- used to create Restful web services, where the controller method return data directly
		in response body
7. @Id
	- Specifies the primary key of an entity

8.  @GeneratedValue strategies
	i. GenerationType.IDENTITY
		- auto increment(automatically generate the primary key)
	ii. GenerationType.SEQUENCE
		- supports sequence
		- custom sequence
	iii. GenerationType.AUTO
		-
